01:04:28,530 --> 01:04:31,390
- Hi.
- Hi. You're on time.

772
01:04:32,100 --> 01:04:36,230
- You forgot?
- No, no, no. I didn't forget.

773
01:04:36,500 --> 01:04:38,300
- Is everything okay?
- What, me?

774
01:04:38,340 --> 01:04:40,030
How are you doing?

775
01:04:40,170 --> 01:04:42,110
I'm good. I'm good.

776
01:04:42,140 --> 01:04:45,370
Would you please stop that?
Will you...

777
01:04:48,950 --> 01:04:51,510
It's probably best for you to leave.

778
01:04:52,050 --> 01:04:53,570
What am I saying?

779
01:04:53,620 --> 01:04:55,920
Okay. Okay, I will go.

780
01:04:56,290 --> 01:04:58,850
Yeah, I'm sorry. I'm having issues.

781
01:05:06,960 --> 01:05:08,120
My coils!

782
01:05:22,110 --> 01:05:23,240
Disperse!

783
01:05:35,490 --> 01:05:40,760
You have abused the sacred art,
and you have abused the Merlin Circle.

784
01:05:41,100 --> 01:05:42,620
Magic isn't a game.

785
01:05:42,970 --> 01:05:44,330
No shortcuts!

786
01:05:44,640 --> 01:05:47,070
Falling in that water
and getting electrocuted,

787
01:05:47,100 --> 01:05:48,970
that's how a sorcerer loses his power!

788
01:05:49,010 --> 01:05:53,030
What rule is that?
Fourteen? Twenty-seven?

789
01:05:53,080 --> 01:05:54,370
I can't even remember!

790
01:05:54,410 --> 01:05:55,810
What difference does it make

791
01:05:55,850 --> 01:05:58,180
if it's obvious
that I can't even control a few mops?

792
01:05:58,220 --> 01:06:00,180
The stronger the man,
the stronger the sorcerer.

793
01:06:00,220 --> 01:06:02,480
Thank you.
Thank you for another useless motto!

794
01:06:02,520 --> 01:06:03,850
I have another one for you.

795
01:06:03,890 --> 01:06:06,650
You will not control your magic
if you will not control yourself.

796
01:06:06,690 --> 01:06:09,320
You need to stop your worrying
and start believing in yourself.

797
01:06:09,690 --> 01:06:10,820
Is that what you do?

798
01:06:10,860 --> 01:06:13,590
- What I do isn't the point.
- I think it is.

799
01:06:13,630 --> 01:06:17,470
I'm convinced you exist purely
to make my life a living hell.

800
01:06:20,240 --> 01:06:22,800
You don't know anything
about a living hell.

801
01:06:28,510 --> 01:06:31,500
- You're making progress.
- No, I'm not making progress.

802
01:06:33,750 --> 01:06:35,310
No ring, right?

803
01:06:39,420 --> 01:06:42,620
No magic.
I can't move the chairs. I can't do it.

804
01:06:44,960 --> 01:06:46,660
It's not me, Balthazar.

805
01:06:46,700 --> 01:06:48,690
I'm sorry! I'm sorry.

806
01:06:50,400 --> 01:06:55,840
I'm not it. I'm not a hero.
I'm not the Prime Merlinean.

807
01:06:55,970 --> 01:06:58,030
I'm just a physics nerd

808
01:06:58,510 --> 01:07:01,970
who looks really, really stupid
in these shoes.

809
01:08:13,150 --> 01:08:14,280
Dave.

810
01:08:16,420 --> 01:08:18,180
What are you doing here?

811
01:08:18,390 --> 01:08:22,350
I saw you outside the coffee shop,
so I followed you.

812
01:08:22,560 --> 01:08:25,430
You looked a little more distressed
than usual.

813
01:08:25,860 --> 01:08:27,160
That bad, huh?

814
01:08:27,630 --> 01:08:29,690
Did you really think that
one botched date

815
01:08:29,730 --> 01:08:32,000
was going to make me
hate you forever?

816
01:08:34,140 --> 01:08:35,230
Yeah.

817
01:08:37,110 --> 01:08:41,070
I do have to ask you this one thing.

818
01:08:43,610 --> 01:08:44,740
What are you doing up here?

819
01:08:45,780 --> 01:08:46,940
Yeah.

820
01:08:48,220 --> 01:08:50,380
A friend of mine brought me here once.

821
01:08:50,990 --> 01:08:54,080
And the height doesn't bother you?

822
01:08:55,390 --> 01:08:57,830
- Are you afraid of heights?
- A little bit, yeah.

823
01:08:58,100 --> 01:08:59,530
Trust me. Here, come on.

824
01:08:59,730 --> 01:09:01,790
Come on. You're good.

825
01:09:02,070 --> 01:09:04,190
- You're good.
- I don't know.

826
01:09:08,610 --> 01:09:09,730
Wow.

827
01:09:10,410 --> 01:09:12,880
Yeah. Wow.

828
01:09:15,350 --> 01:09:18,870
Do you remember when you drew
King Kong on the bus window?

829
01:09:18,920 --> 01:09:21,320
And he lined up
with the Empire State Building?

830
01:09:22,820 --> 01:09:23,910
You remember that?

831
01:09:24,520 --> 01:09:25,950
It was cool.

832
01:09:28,190 --> 01:09:31,420
You saw the world in your own way.

833
01:09:32,360 --> 01:09:33,920
I was just trying to impress you.

834
01:09:35,770 --> 01:09:39,830
Well, it worked.
Not bad for a 10-year-old kid.

835
01:09:41,140 --> 01:09:43,400
Yeah, right. What happened?

836
01:09:44,910 --> 01:09:48,000
- What? What do you mean?
- The bitter irony of the fact

837
01:09:48,050 --> 01:09:51,780
that 10-year-old me
is far cooler than 20-year-old me.

838
01:09:52,580 --> 01:09:55,610
I think 20-year-old Dave is...
He's all right.

839
01:09:56,390 --> 01:10:00,880
Like, "all right" all right,
or "all right!" all right?

840
01:10:03,760 --> 01:10:07,460
I think he is somewhere in the middle.

841
01:10:08,170 --> 01:10:11,030
That's a diplomatic answer.

842
01:10:12,170 --> 01:10:13,430
And thank you.

843
01:10:23,150 --> 01:10:24,940
- Hey.
- Hello.

844
01:10:25,150 --> 01:10:26,210
I'm sorry.

845
01:10:26,750 --> 01:10:29,050
I think you and I need to have a talk.

846
01:10:29,620 --> 01:10:32,590
No apology necessary. Let us move on.

847
01:10:33,160 --> 01:10:34,520
You're a diamond, mate.

848
01:10:49,540 --> 01:10:51,030
Surprisingly well done.

849
01:10:51,210 --> 01:10:52,640
Now go find the Grimhold.

850
01:10:56,580 --> 01:10:59,780
You seem to have rather a soft spot
for that boy.

851
01:11:00,180 --> 01:11:02,550
Has Balthazar made a new friend?

852
01:11:03,520 --> 01:11:04,820
I don't see the Grimhold.

853
01:11:04,860 --> 01:11:07,520
That's because you're using your eyes.

854
01:11:07,860 --> 01:11:09,520
Clever Balthazar.

855
01:11:10,390 --> 01:11:12,390
Always up to his little tricks.

856
01:11:34,750 --> 01:11:35,840
Found it.

857
01:11:39,460 --> 01:11:41,120
It's lighter than I remember.

858
01:11:42,790 --> 01:11:44,660
We once fought together, Maxim.

859
01:11:44,730 --> 01:11:46,700
A lot's happened since those days.

860
01:11:46,930 --> 01:11:50,020
- This isn't about that.
- Oh, yes, it is, Balthazar.

861
01:11:50,830 --> 01:11:52,300
It's always been about that.

862
01:11:53,040 --> 01:11:57,740
Veronica chose you instead of me,
the great Balthazar Blake,

863
01:11:59,780 --> 01:12:01,330
my best friend.

864
01:12:02,110 --> 01:12:06,410
Well, I'm going to let you
watch me release Morgana.

865
01:12:06,720 --> 01:12:09,880
Let you watch your world
crumble into nothing!

866
01:12:32,080 --> 01:12:33,700
Drake. Let's go.

867
01:12:36,550 --> 01:12:38,810
- Nice catch.
- I owed you one.

868
01:12:39,450 --> 01:12:41,540
- They got the doll.
- Let's get it back.

869
01:12:45,620 --> 01:12:46,880
Hang on.

870
01:12:47,720 --> 01:12:48,850
Hang on, Tank.

871
01:13:04,270 --> 01:13:05,330
Go left.

872
01:13:10,880 --> 01:13:12,820
Whoa! What the...

873
01:13:12,850 --> 01:13:15,550
Horvath!
He's in here somewhere.

874
01:13:15,650 --> 01:13:18,310
Wait. He has the power
to turn his car into a taxi?

875
01:13:18,590 --> 01:13:20,520
Use your ring
and lock in on the Grimhold.

876
01:13:20,560 --> 01:13:23,550
- Remember, it moves with the ring.
- Okay, yeah. Right, right, right.

877
01:13:31,640 --> 01:13:32,730
Go! Go!

878
01:13:35,970 --> 01:13:37,030
Here they come!

879
01:13:42,750 --> 01:13:43,840
Whoa!

880
01:13:43,880 --> 01:13:44,970
What the heck!

881
01:13:46,380 --> 01:13:48,250
Nice one!

882
01:13:54,060 --> 01:13:56,030
- Hey! Well, look at that.
- Hang on.

883
01:14:03,930 --> 01:14:04,960
Oh, my God.

884
01:14:05,440 --> 01:14:06,560
Take the tunnel.

885
01:14:19,850 --> 01:14:21,720
What is that, smoke?

886
01:14:27,420 --> 01:14:29,090
Oh, come on!

887
01:14:41,370 --> 01:14:43,000
Time for a little revenge.

888
01:14:50,550 --> 01:14:53,180
- What the heck is this?
- Yes, we drove through a mirror.

889
01:14:53,220 --> 01:14:55,210
- We're trapped in a reverse world.
- So...

890
01:14:55,250 --> 01:14:57,850
It is, it is. Horvath's payback
for the bathroom mirror.

891
01:14:57,890 --> 01:14:59,250
No, no. We won't die as long as

892
01:14:59,290 --> 01:15:00,780
- we get out of here soon.
- Okay.

893
01:15:00,820 --> 01:15:03,320
- By driving through our own reflection.
- Fantastic.

894
01:15:03,560 --> 01:15:05,360
There. In the window.
- This is it.

895
01:15:15,270 --> 01:15:16,760
No, no, no, no, no. You're not...

896
01:15:17,010 --> 01:15:19,030
- Here we go.
- We're not going to make that!

897
01:15:19,880 --> 01:15:21,870
We're not...

898
01:15:42,230 --> 01:15:43,460
Hello, Balthazar.

899
01:15:44,600 --> 01:15:45,900
Oh, man. Oh, man.

900
01:15:45,940 --> 01:15:47,600
No, no, no.
Back up. Back up. Back up. Back up.

901
01:15:47,640 --> 01:15:49,610
Back up. Back up. Back up. Back up.

902
01:15:51,710 --> 01:15:52,800
Oh, man.

903
01:15:53,810 --> 01:15:55,470
I've got an idea. I've got an idea.

904
01:15:55,810 --> 01:15:57,540
- Dave, don't.
- Please just let me do it.

905
01:16:00,250 --> 01:16:03,150
- What?
- '73 Pinto? This is your idea?

906
01:16:03,190 --> 01:16:06,920
No! No. My idea was to turn their car
into a beater.

907
01:16:14,760 --> 01:16:15,960
- Finish it.
- Right!

908
01:16:25,780 --> 01:16:27,070
I think he stopped.

909
01:16:38,590 --> 01:16:42,080
Hold on, Tank.
Hold on, Tank. I got you, buddy.

910
01:16:42,190 --> 01:16:43,720
...walked away.

911
01:17:01,510 --> 01:17:02,600
Hey!

912
01:17:03,750 --> 01:17:06,840
I'm sorry.
I thought you were someone else.

913
01:17:10,620 --> 01:17:12,050
Where's Horvath?

914
01:17:12,290 --> 01:17:13,950
Did he get away?

915
01:17:13,990 --> 01:17:16,620
Where's the Grimhold? Who was that?

916
01:17:19,100 --> 01:17:20,530
That was her, wasn't it?

917
01:17:21,200 --> 01:17:23,030
The third apprentice.

918
01:17:26,400 --> 01:17:30,270
For centuries, Veronica, Horvath and I
were the only thing standing

919
01:17:30,310 --> 01:17:32,940
between Morgana
and man's destruction.

920
01:17:33,810 --> 01:17:37,610
Our friendship and our magic were
what Veronica and I depended on.

921
01:17:39,750 --> 01:17:40,840
You fell for her, didn't you?

922
01:17:43,350 --> 01:17:44,910
I fell for her.

923
01:17:47,760 --> 01:17:50,850
<i>Like you,
all Veronica wanted was to be normal.</i>

924
01:17:51,900 --> 01:17:54,860
<i>Normal things, normal life.</i>

925
01:17:57,030 --> 01:17:58,260
<i>I fell.</i>

926
01:18:01,200 --> 01:18:02,640
And so did Horvath.

927
01:18:05,080 --> 01:18:07,200
That's why Horvath betrayed us.

928
01:18:07,580 --> 01:18:09,550
For 1,000 years,

929
01:18:09,580 --> 01:18:11,910
you've been carrying her
around with you.

930
01:18:12,280 --> 01:18:13,910
In the Grimhold.

931
01:18:15,250 --> 01:18:18,120
I was going to give this to her
that night.

932
01:18:26,730 --> 01:18:28,100
I'm sorry.

933
01:18:31,430 --> 01:18:32,800
Okay, Balthazar.

934
01:18:33,140 --> 01:18:37,540
We are going to get Veronica out
and destroy Morgana.

935
01:18:39,640 --> 01:18:41,080
What's happened to you?

936
01:18:41,510 --> 01:18:42,570
Nothing.

937
01:18:42,850 --> 01:18:44,310
You're still a bad liar.

938
01:18:44,780 --> 01:18:48,380
- Why does everyone...
- You know, I am glad she likes you.

939
01:18:48,420 --> 01:18:51,510
No, I am not surprised. Only glad.

940
01:18:52,420 --> 01:18:54,890
There's nothing like it, is there?

941
01:18:57,090 --> 01:19:00,890
Put your old man shoes back on.

942
01:19:01,830 --> 01:19:02,960
We have some work to do.

943
01:19:07,340 --> 01:19:08,800
Are all the satellite dishes
in position?

944
01:19:08,840 --> 01:19:09,960
All lined up.

945
01:19:10,340 --> 01:19:13,370
I chipped my mani, which is not cool.

946
01:19:13,410 --> 01:19:15,340
No, I imagine it's not.

947
01:19:16,110 --> 01:19:19,510
Inside there lies our next coworker.

948
01:19:19,850 --> 01:19:23,910
Abigail Williams,
a little witch who put Salem on the map.

949
01:19:24,590 --> 01:19:27,180
Once she's out,
we're at the Morgana shell.

950
01:19:27,220 --> 01:19:30,920
Now that's going to take a lot of time
and energy to crack.

951
01:19:30,960 --> 01:19:32,480
So what are we going to do?

952
01:19:32,530 --> 01:19:34,760
Have you heard of the Parasite Spell?

953
01:19:36,530 --> 01:19:40,260
Sorry, I forgot
your education's somewhat lacking.

954
01:19:40,300 --> 01:19:42,770
Yeah, I prefer to go more by instinct.

955
01:19:42,810 --> 01:19:44,710
You know, what feels right.

956
01:19:44,840 --> 01:19:49,210
Very good. Well, the Parasite Spell
is a rather nasty piece of business.

957
01:19:49,710 --> 01:19:53,110
It originated in Haiti, if memory serves.

958
01:19:53,650 --> 01:19:57,710
It enables one sorcerer
to steal the energy from another.

959
01:20:03,030 --> 01:20:05,860
Well, you weren't really using it,
were you?

960
01:20:17,010 --> 01:20:18,270
Excuse me?

961
01:20:18,440 --> 01:20:19,970
I'd like to make a request.

962
01:20:20,540 --> 01:20:23,880
<i>I just finished my show.
But maybe next time, okay?</i>

963
01:20:32,560 --> 01:20:35,020
I said I'd like to make a request.

964
01:20:40,030 --> 01:20:41,050
All right.

965
01:20:42,730 --> 01:20:46,360
When Morgana is released,
no matter what happens,

966
01:20:47,200 --> 01:20:50,660
promise me you'll do whatever it takes
to destroy her.

967
01:20:52,340 --> 01:20:53,400
I promise.

968
01:20:54,980 --> 01:20:57,910
And for the record,
you wear the old guy shoes very well.

969
01:20:59,050 --> 01:21:00,850
My feet disagree with you,
but thank you.

970
01:21:02,690 --> 01:21:03,780
Knuckle bump.

971
01:21:07,220 --> 01:21:08,450
Might as well.

972
01:21:09,930 --> 01:21:14,520
Now that I have kidnapped the girl
for you, is it time to release Morgana?

973
01:21:14,560 --> 01:21:16,690
I'll give her your regards.

974
01:21:17,600 --> 01:21:20,360
Mr. Horvath,
have I done something wrong?

975
01:21:22,170 --> 01:21:23,230
Not at all.

976
01:21:23,510 --> 01:21:29,240
I need your power to free Morgana.
I just don't need you.

977
01:21:30,650 --> 01:21:32,310
Well, that's two.

978
01:21:33,080 --> 01:21:34,170
One more to go.

979
01:21:45,300 --> 01:21:47,260
That's horrifying.

980
01:21:47,300 --> 01:21:50,490
Let's just find the Grimhold
and be done with it.

981
01:22:04,050 --> 01:22:06,740
Battery Park. The Rising.

982
01:22:15,230 --> 01:22:16,450
Persian Quickrug.

983
01:22:17,430 --> 01:22:19,420
And he thinks I'm old-fashioned.

984
01:22:23,070 --> 01:22:24,560
Ostentatious.

985
01:22:34,480 --> 01:22:37,910
Ooh... Uh-huh.

986
01:22:45,620 --> 01:22:47,280
Nothing, nothing.

987
01:22:50,260 --> 01:22:51,960
So that's Morgana.

988
01:22:55,900 --> 01:22:57,200
Veronica.

989
01:23:09,380 --> 01:23:10,740
Balthazar?

990
01:23:11,150 --> 01:23:14,340
That was easy.
Come on, Dave. You know the drill.

991
01:23:14,550 --> 01:23:16,180
Give me what I want, and I'll let her go.

992
01:23:16,220 --> 01:23:17,910
Dave, what is going on?

993
01:23:17,950 --> 01:23:19,320
It's gonna be okay.
You're gonna be okay.

994
01:23:19,360 --> 01:23:20,380
No, she's not!

995
01:23:21,320 --> 01:23:24,520
She's going to be ground up
into chunks and fed to the cat

996
01:23:24,560 --> 01:23:27,720
unless you give me Merlin's ring
and the Grimhold.

997
01:23:27,760 --> 01:23:30,820
Balthazar?
He's busy admiring the decor.

998
01:23:30,870 --> 01:23:32,660
So what's it going to be?

999
01:24:02,100 --> 01:24:03,220
Here.

1000
01:24:05,100 --> 01:24:06,190
Take it.

1001
01:24:11,310 --> 01:24:13,300
- You're okay?
- Merlin's ring.

1002
01:24:13,810 --> 01:24:16,800
It's been a while
since I've been this close to it.

1003
01:24:17,550 --> 01:24:19,070
I wonder if it still works.

1004
01:24:25,020 --> 01:24:27,620
- You all right?
- Yeah, I think so.

1005
01:24:34,200 --> 01:24:35,260
The Grimhold?

1006
01:24:39,240 --> 01:24:40,430
I see.

1007
01:24:41,640 --> 01:24:43,730
He took my ring.

1008
01:24:44,640 --> 01:24:46,630
He was gonna kill Becky.

1009
01:24:47,610 --> 01:24:49,600
I'm so sorry, Balthazar.

1010
01:24:50,610 --> 01:24:53,050
I would have done
the same thing, Dave.

1011
01:24:57,050 --> 01:24:58,280
Where are you going?

1012
01:24:58,320 --> 01:25:01,220
Battery Park.
Horvath's going to release Morgana.

1013
01:25:01,260 --> 01:25:05,160
Well, you can't take him on
and Morgana at the same time. That's...

1014
01:25:05,190 --> 01:25:07,860
- You literally can't.
- I have to try.

1015
01:25:07,900 --> 01:25:09,460
Well, then I'm going with you.

1016
01:25:10,000 --> 01:25:11,490
Without any magic?

1017
01:25:11,870 --> 01:25:13,530
He has your ring.

1018
01:25:13,640 --> 01:25:14,800
I'm going alone.

1019
01:25:17,310 --> 01:25:19,770
No, that's a normal thing for him.

1020
01:25:22,750 --> 01:25:25,270
No one knows
how much time they have

1021
01:25:26,450 --> 01:25:29,350
to be with the people
that are the most important.

1022
01:25:30,120 --> 01:25:31,420
Enjoy it.

1023
01:25:45,300 --> 01:25:47,700
That guy just flew away on an eagle!

1024
01:25:47,740 --> 01:25:49,260
- I...
- A steel eagle.

1025
01:25:49,310 --> 01:25:50,930
Becky, I wanted to talk to you
about this.

1026
01:25:50,970 --> 01:25:53,370
I just haven't known where to start.

1027
01:25:54,540 --> 01:25:56,440
I'm just happy you're okay.

1028
01:25:57,250 --> 01:26:01,910
Look, Dave.
If you can just tell me the truth,

1029
01:26:02,250 --> 01:26:05,850
then I promise I will do my best
to understand.

1030
01:26:07,520 --> 01:26:11,690
Okay. The first thing you should know
about me is that I'm a sorcerer.

1031
01:26:14,560 --> 01:26:15,720
Okay.

1032
01:26:15,770 --> 01:26:20,130
I can conjure and shoot plasma bolts
out of my hand.

1033
01:26:20,800 --> 01:26:23,070
I can speed time up, slow it down,

1034
01:26:23,310 --> 01:26:27,540
varying degrees of levitation.
It's all very magical.

1035
01:26:29,280 --> 01:26:33,510
And I thought my last boyfriend
was different 'cause he wore a scarf.

1036
01:26:38,750 --> 01:26:43,350
- Baby, I'll just come back. Okay?
- Okay.

1037
01:26:43,390 --> 01:26:46,880
- I'll see you in a minute.
- Okay. All right. I'm here.

1038
01:26:50,770 --> 01:26:51,990
Bad time, Dave.

1039
01:26:52,370 --> 01:26:53,840
Bennet. Thank God you answered.

1040
01:26:53,970 --> 01:26:55,440
<i>I got a real emergency on my hands.</i>

1041
01:26:55,470 --> 01:26:58,300
<i>I need you to meet me
at my lab right now!</i>

1042
01:26:59,780 --> 01:27:03,070
- Becky, I got to let you out.
- What? Let me out?

1043
01:27:03,650 --> 01:27:04,740
Okay.

1044
01:27:04,780 --> 01:27:07,870
I think I know how to defeat them
without any magic.

1045
01:27:07,920 --> 01:27:09,320
How?

1046
01:27:09,350 --> 01:27:11,250
The rings on Horvath's cane.

1047
01:27:11,290 --> 01:27:14,780
He put them there to gain more power,
but they make him a better conductor.

1048
01:27:14,820 --> 01:27:18,230
Dave, I have no idea
what you're talking about.

1049
01:27:19,030 --> 01:27:21,360
All right, Rebecca, here it is.

1050
01:27:22,270 --> 01:27:25,670
Many evil sorcerers will be
raised from the dead tonight.

1051
01:27:25,900 --> 01:27:30,270
So, basically, Morgana is trying
to destroy the world as we know it.

1052
01:27:31,370 --> 01:27:32,740
Oh, just that.

1053
01:27:33,240 --> 01:27:36,580
This is really dangerous.
I can't bring you into it.

1054
01:27:37,680 --> 01:27:39,740
Well, I think I'm already into it.

1055
01:27:40,620 --> 01:27:44,350
And besides, if you blow it,
we're all gonna die anyway, right?

1056
01:27:45,190 --> 01:27:46,710
I want to come with you.

1057
01:27:48,820 --> 01:27:49,980
You're sexy.

1058
01:27:52,730 --> 01:27:56,100
- I got all the Tesla coil remotes.
- Thanks, brother. I appreciate it.

1059
01:27:56,470 --> 01:27:58,630
Oh! I found this after we hung up.

1060
01:27:59,670 --> 01:28:01,430
It was on the desk.

1061
01:28:02,640 --> 01:28:04,610
"Give this to Veronica. Balthazar. "

1062
01:28:11,410 --> 01:28:14,650
I don't think Balthazar's planning
on coming back.

1063
01:28:16,590 --> 01:28:19,350
I don't know
what you're into here, Dave,

1064
01:28:19,720 --> 01:28:24,250
but whatever it is,
you are definitely participating!

1065
01:28:25,160 --> 01:28:28,030
Thank you, Bennet. I appreciate that.
We should go.

1066
01:28:41,380 --> 01:28:43,070
Now is The Rising.

1067
01:28:45,450 --> 01:28:46,510
Now is the time.

1068
01:29:15,850 --> 01:29:17,140
Veronica.

1069
01:29:20,020 --> 01:29:22,540
It's me, Horvath. Morgana.

1070
01:29:23,620 --> 01:29:25,780
No need to look so pathetic.

1071
01:29:28,320 --> 01:29:29,450
Destroy that thing.

1072
01:29:29,490 --> 01:29:31,720
I never want to see it again.

1073
01:29:33,830 --> 01:29:37,420
I cannot raise the dead
until the circle is complete.

1074
01:30:03,190 --> 01:30:06,680
- No way. Man alive!
- What?

1075
01:30:06,930 --> 01:30:09,260
Are you telling me
you honestly don't see that?

1076
01:30:09,300 --> 01:30:10,360
No. See what?

1077
01:30:10,400 --> 01:30:13,370
I think they're using the satellite dishes
on the tops of the buildings

1078
01:30:13,400 --> 01:30:16,100
to direct and amplify
the electromagnetic energy.

1079
01:30:16,140 --> 01:30:17,770
All right, we're pulling over.
We're pulling over.

1080
01:30:22,340 --> 01:30:24,210
Becky, I need you to do me a favor.

1081
01:30:24,650 --> 01:30:27,880
I need you to go up
to the very top of that thing.

1082
01:30:29,250 --> 01:30:30,340
Great.

1083
01:30:30,450 --> 01:30:33,790
You got to move that antenna
and just disrupt the signal.

1084
01:30:34,360 --> 01:30:35,520
Okay. Right.

1085
01:30:37,130 --> 01:30:38,530
Hey, Becky.

1086
01:30:38,830 --> 01:30:41,730
Do you remember that letter I wrote
when we were 10 years old?

1087
01:30:41,760 --> 01:30:42,890
Friend or girlfriend?

1088
01:30:43,270 --> 01:30:45,700
I never saw what you checked,

1089
01:30:46,700 --> 01:30:48,640
so in case I die tonight,
could you please tell me?

1090
01:30:50,510 --> 01:30:51,670
Don't die and I'll tell you.

1091
01:30:53,210 --> 01:30:55,180
Oh, yeah, okay.

1092
01:31:29,480 --> 01:31:30,600
Balthazar.

1093
01:31:34,520 --> 01:31:37,850
- Enough of your old tricks, Balthazar.
- As you wish.

1094
01:31:47,060 --> 01:31:50,930
Time was, things were pretty even
between us, Balthazar.

1095
01:31:51,900 --> 01:31:53,270
As you can see,

1096
01:31:54,570 --> 01:31:56,900
I've acquired some new jewelry.

1097
01:32:01,240 --> 01:32:03,270
I'm coming, buddy.
I'm coming. I'm coming.

1098
01:32:03,680 --> 01:32:08,740
All right, what... What is this?
What am I looking at? No!

1099
01:32:10,890 --> 01:32:13,410
And a walker. Of course she has a...

1100
01:32:14,090 --> 01:32:15,560
Okay.

1101
01:32:17,360 --> 01:32:18,590
Oh, boy.

1102
01:32:21,260 --> 01:32:26,700
A matador gored by a bull
can take up to three days to die.

1103
01:32:27,640 --> 01:32:29,900
Sounds unpleasant, doesn't it?

1104
01:33:16,790 --> 01:33:18,510
The circle is nearly complete.

1105
01:33:18,990 --> 01:33:21,010
It must be awful, Balthazar.

1106
01:33:21,360 --> 01:33:24,520
All these years,
fighting to stop this one moment

1107
01:33:25,190 --> 01:33:26,890
and then coming up short.

1108
01:34:06,370 --> 01:34:07,390
That's my car.

1109
01:34:24,390 --> 01:34:25,610
Oh!

1110
01:34:25,650 --> 01:34:26,810
Thank you!

1111
01:34:37,470 --> 01:34:38,520
We're too late.

1112
01:34:56,890 --> 01:34:57,980
Veronica.

1113
01:35:02,320 --> 01:35:03,620
Is she...

1114
01:35:06,130 --> 01:35:07,600
They're both still with us.

1115
01:35:36,360 --> 01:35:38,620
Balthazar, what have you done?

1116
01:35:39,760 --> 01:35:41,160
What you did for me.

1117
01:35:45,230 --> 01:35:47,000
- Remember your promise.
- Balthazar, no.

1118
01:35:47,040 --> 01:35:49,370
You'll do whatever it takes
to destroy Morgana.

1119
01:35:49,410 --> 01:35:53,210
No. No, I can't.
I won't lock you in this thing.

1120
01:35:53,410 --> 01:35:54,840
Neither will I.

1121
01:35:56,010 --> 01:35:57,380
How sweet.

1122
01:36:09,830 --> 01:36:10,880
Oh, man.

1123
01:36:13,900 --> 01:36:16,870
- And now we end this.
- No!

1124
01:36:22,600 --> 01:36:23,830
No way.

1125
01:36:29,980 --> 01:36:31,070
No ring.

1126
01:36:31,480 --> 01:36:32,710
It is you.

1127
01:36:33,080 --> 01:36:34,380
The Prime Merlinean!

1128
01:36:37,650 --> 01:36:38,850
Fools!

1129
01:36:40,920 --> 01:36:42,220
Veronica!

1130
01:36:51,430 --> 01:36:52,630
Now it's my turn.

1131
01:37:01,440 --> 01:37:03,340
Is that the best that you can do?

1132
01:37:04,850 --> 01:37:05,940
I sure hope not.

1133
01:37:24,600 --> 01:37:27,590
And now it's my turn.

1134
01:37:51,490 --> 01:37:52,590
Come on.

1135
01:37:59,200 --> 01:38:00,260
Climb.

1136
01:38:04,310 --> 01:38:06,570
You have Merlin's powers,

1137
01:38:06,910 --> 01:38:09,710
but you don't have his strength
or his skill.

1138
01:38:09,850 --> 01:38:11,610
You are still weak.

1139
01:38:12,550 --> 01:38:13,740
But I'm not alone.

1140
01:38:13,980 --> 01:38:17,180
I brought a little science with me. Now!

1141
01:39:02,260 --> 01:39:04,930
I did it! Balthazar, I actually did it!

1142
01:39:16,040 --> 01:39:17,410
He's gone.

1143
01:39:21,720 --> 01:39:23,650
He completed his quest.

1144
01:39:26,190 --> 01:39:30,180
No, no, no, no.
It's not over. He can't die.

1145
01:39:30,690 --> 01:39:32,960
I just... Not now.

1146
01:39:36,370 --> 01:39:37,630
Come on.

1147
01:39:56,080 --> 01:39:57,850
That's not good enough.

1148
01:40:00,720 --> 01:40:03,160
Veronica, would you please step back?

1149
01:40:03,890 --> 01:40:07,090
If Morgana can stop his heart,
maybe I can start it.

1150
01:40:13,540 --> 01:40:16,270
All right, here we go, bud.
Here we go. Listen.

1151
01:40:16,310 --> 01:40:19,670
You... You with all your stupid rules!

1152
01:40:20,180 --> 01:40:22,300
And all those old man shoes.

1153
01:40:22,340 --> 01:40:25,040
And your constantly saving me
with that look in your eyes.

1154
01:40:25,510 --> 01:40:26,780
Come on!

1155
01:40:27,420 --> 01:40:28,680
Come on!

1156
01:40:29,620 --> 01:40:30,810
Come on.

1157
01:40:32,550 --> 01:40:33,950
Come on.

1158
01:40:46,940 --> 01:40:48,530
I had a dream.

1159
01:40:51,610 --> 01:40:55,770
You were insulting me, Dave.
Repeatedly.

1160
01:40:56,510 --> 01:40:59,480
Me? That's pretty weird, huh?

1161
01:40:59,880 --> 01:41:02,850
No, kind of makes sense.

1162
01:41:02,880 --> 01:41:04,010
Yeah.

1163
01:41:08,620 --> 01:41:11,090
- Thank you.
- Welcome back, old man.

1164
01:41:12,330 --> 01:41:13,760
You're here.

1165
01:41:37,120 --> 01:41:38,250
Dave!

1166
01:41:42,620 --> 01:41:46,060
- You did it!
- I know. And I'm still alive.

1167
01:41:46,090 --> 01:41:48,360
And, surprisingly, so am I.

1168
01:41:48,400 --> 01:41:51,700
I know. Oh, the note. Right.

1169
01:41:51,900 --> 01:41:53,700
- Friend or girlfriend?
- I don't care.

1170
01:41:59,540 --> 01:42:01,870
Girlfriend. Definitely girlfriend.

1171
01:42:06,920 --> 01:42:11,010
Would you like to have breakfast
with me? In France?

1172
01:42:11,650 --> 01:42:12,710
France?

1173
01:42:16,260 --> 01:42:17,950
Yeah, I got us a ride.

1174
01:42:18,760 --> 01:42:20,590
Okay, you're fun.

1175
01:42:26,170 --> 01:42:29,540
Becky, there's something I forgot
to mention to you.

1176
01:42:29,570 --> 01:42:32,540
I really have no idea
how to land this thing.

